						               													<description>You have just one minute to talk on a given subject - don't let anyone else interrupt. All Wafflers are welcome!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A host is needed as a timekeeper who will also settle disputes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The host picks a card at random and reads out the topic on the card. The first player has to speak for as long as he can (up to a maximum of one minute) on that subject. Other players listen and can challenge for: Hesitation, Deviation or Repetition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player challenges correctly he can then take over the role of speaker. Whoever is speaking at the end of one minute earns two points. Whoever has most points at the end, when everyone has had an equal number of chances to be first speaker, is the overall winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
